```js
const axios = require("axios");

  method: "GET",
  url: "/api/v3/countries",
  headers: {

})
```

```go
package main

import (
    "bytes"
    "fmt"
    "io/ioutil"
    "net/http"
)

func main() {
    client := &http.Client{}

    req, err := http.NewRequest("GET", "/api/v3/countries", nil)
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Println(err)
        return
    }
    req.Header = map[string][]string{
        "Authorization": {"Bearer {{token}}"}
    }
    resp, err := client.Do(req)
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Println(err)
        return
    }
    defer resp.Body.Close()

    body, err := ioutil.ReadAll(resp.Body)
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Println(err)
        return
    }
    fmt.Println(string(body))
}
```

```go
package main

import (
    "bytes"
    "fmt"
    "io/ioutil"
    "net/http"
)

func main() {
    client := &http.Client{}

    req, err := http.NewRequest("GET", "/api/v3/industries", nil)
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Println(err)
        return
    }
    req.Header = map[string][]string{
        "Authorization": {"Bearer {{token}}"}
    }
    resp, err := client.Do(req)
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Println(err)
        return
    }
    defer resp.Body.Close()

    body, err := ioutil.ReadAll(resp.Body)
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Println(err)
        return
    }
    fmt.Println(string(body))
}
```

```go
package main

import (
    "bytes"
    "fmt"
    "io/ioutil"
    "net/http"
)

func main() {
    client := &http.Client{}

    req, err := http.NewRequest("GET", "/api/v3/currencies", nil)
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Println(err)
        return
    }
    req.Header = map[string][]string{
        "Authorization": {"Bearer {{token}}"}
    }
    resp, err := client.Do(req)
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Println(err)
        return
    }
    defer resp.Body.Close()

    body, err := ioutil.ReadAll(resp.Body)
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Println(err)
        return
    }
    fmt.Println(string(body))
}
```

```go
package main

import (
    "bytes"
    "fmt"
    "io/ioutil"
    "net/http"
)

func main() {
    client := &http.Client{}

    req, err := http.NewRequest("GET", "/api/v3/current-business", nil)
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Println(err)
        return
    }
    req.Header = map[string][]string{
        "Authorization": {"Bearer {{token}}"}
    }
    resp, err := client.Do(req)
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Println(err)
        return
    }
    defer resp.Body.Close()

    body, err := ioutil.ReadAll(resp.Body)
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Println(err)
        return
    }
    fmt.Println(string(body))
}
```

```go
package main

import (

func main() {
    client := &http.Client{}

    var jsonStr = []byte(`{

  "industry_id": 1,
  "region_id": "",
  "employee_size": "",
  "email": "",
  "logo_url": "",
  "invoice_id": "",
  "address": "",
  "phone_number": "",
  "bank_name": "",
  "account_name": "",
  "account_number": ""
}`)
    req, err := http.NewRequest("POST", "/api/v3/update-business", bytes.NewBuffer(jsonStr))
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Println(err)
        return
    }
    req.Header = map[string][]string{
        "Accept": {"application/json"},
"Authorization": {"Bearer {{token}}"}
    }
    resp, err := client.Do(req)
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Println(err)
        return
    }
    defer resp.Body.Close()

    body, err := ioutil.ReadAll(resp.Body)
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Println(err)
        return
    }
    fmt.Println(string(body))
}
```
